Class MultiGreeter

  • java.lang.Object
    • edu.metrostate.ics240.p1.jph142.MultiGreeter

  • public class MultiGreeter
extends java.lang.Object
    MultiGreeter is a collection class that stores data objects for holding and manipulating multiple String greetings.
    Author:
    John

    • Constructor Summary

      Constructors 
      Constructor and Description
      MultiGreeter()
      Initializes this Greeter to size 1, this is the max greetings this Greeter can hold.
      MultiGreeter(int maxGreetings)
      Initializes this Greeter to size maxGreetings, this is the max greetings this Greeter can hold.

    • Method Summary

      All Methods Instance Methods Concrete Methods 
      Modifier and Type Method and Description
      boolean add(java.lang.String greeting)
      If this Greeter is not at capacity, adds a greeting String to this Greeter and returns true.
      java.lang.String[] getGreetings()
      Generates and returns a String[] containing all the greetings in this Greeter the size of which is number of greetings in this Greeter.
      int getMaxGreetings()
      Gets the maximum number of greetings this Greeter can hold.
      int getNumGreetings()
      Gets the number of greetings currently in this Greeter.
      java.lang.String greet()
      Returns a salutation in the form “greetingString, World!” if greetingString is null or empty, returns "Hello, World!"
      java.lang.String greet(java.lang.String name)
      Returns a salutation in the form “greetingString, name!” if greetingString or name is null or empty, they will be assigned "Hello" and "World" respectively.
